What is Spring Boot DevTools? (Simple Explanation)
Spring Boot DevTools is a tool that helps developers by auto-restarting the application when code changes, making development faster and easier.

Think of it Like This:
Imagine you are writing a document, but every time you make a small change, you have to close and reopen the file to see the update. That would be annoying, right? ğŸ˜©

Spring Boot DevTools removes this pain by automatically reloading your application whenever you make changes! ğŸš€

Why Use DevTools?
âœ… Auto-restart: No need to stop & restart the app manually.
âœ… LiveReload Support: Auto-refresh browser when frontend changes.
âœ… Disables Caching: Helps in debugging by showing real-time changes.
âœ… Works Only in Development: Won't affect production performance.

